top_reason\":\"tool_use\",\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":3,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":2354,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":25387,\"output_tokens\":81,\"server_tool_use\":{\"web_search_requests\":0,\"web_fetch_requests\":0},\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":2354,\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0},\"inference_geo\":\"\",\"iterations\":[],\"speed\":\"standard\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYnmYrwqCbgdnFEaNeD5E\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"9b6a5031-063b-4bad-8649-126f30d72dd8\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-07T00:25:10.720Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"9b6a5031-063b-4bad-8649-126f30d72dd8\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"a81178c2-3cee-4c17-bcb1-f86a790fe8fd\",\"version\":\"2.1.71\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/e2e-triage-local-only\",\"slug\":\"luminous-plotting-creek\",\"type\":\"progress\",\"data\":{\"type\":\"hook_progress\",\"hookEvent\":\"PostToolUse\",\"hookName\":\"PostToolUse:Read\",\"command\":\"callback\"},\"parentToolUseID\":\"toolu_01GjkPUy4m21f5zbYWJ7oWZB\",\"toolUseID\":\"toolu_01GjkPUy4m21f5zbYWJ7oWZB\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-07T00:25:10.740Z\",\"uuid\":\"c6a4ef86-f5fa-4820-88f3-437b0893158c\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"9b6a5031-063b-4bad-8649-126f30d72dd8\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"a81178c2-3cee-4c17-bcb1-f86a790fe8fd\",\"version\":\"2.1.71\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/e2e-triage-local-only\",\"slug\":\"luminous-plotting-creek\",\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01GjkPUy4m21f5zbYWJ7oWZB\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1→---\\n     2→name: e2e-triage\\n     3→description: Triage E2E test failures — run locally with mise, classify flaky vs real bug. Presents findings and applies fixes in-place.\\n     4→---\\n     5→\\n     6→# E2E Triage\\n     7→\\n     8→Triage E2E test failures with **re-run verification**. Analyzes artifacts and re-runs failing tests locally to distinguish flaky from real bugs. Presents findings interactively and applies fixes directly in the working tree.\\n     9→\\n    10→---\\n    11→\\n    12→## Step L1: Parse User Input\\n    13→\\n    14→The user provides one or more of:\\n    15→- **Test name(s)** — e.g., `TestInteractiveMultiStep`\\n    16→- **`--agent <agent>`** — optional, defaults to all agents that previously failed\\n    17→- **A local artifact path** — skip straight to analysis of existing artifacts\\n    18→\\n    19→**Cost warning:** Real E2E tests consume API tokens. Before running, confirm with the user unless they provided specific test names (implying intent to run).\\n    20→\\n    21→## Step L2: First Run\\n    22→\\n    23→```bash\\n    24→mise run test:e2e --agent <agent> <TestName>\\n    25→```\\n    26→\\n    27→Capture the artifact directory from the `artifacts: <path>` output line.\\n    28→\\n    29→## Step L3: Re-run on Failure\\n    30→\\n    31→If the test **passes** on first run: report as passing, done for this test.\\n    32→\\n    33→If the test **fails**: run a **second time** with the same parameters.\\n    34→\\n    35→## Step L4: Tiebreaker (if needed)\\n    36→\\n    37→If results are **split** (1 pass, 1 fail): run a **third time** as tiebreaker.\\n    38→\\n    39→## Step L5: Collect Results\\n    40→\\n    41→For each test+agent pair, record: `(test, agent, run_1_result, run_2_result, [run_3_result])`\\n    42→\\n    43→Proceed to **Shared Analysis** (Step 1 below).\\n    44→\\n    45→---\\n    46→\\n    47→## Shared Analysis & Classification\\n    48→\\n    49→### Step 1: Analyze Each Failure\\n    50→\\n    51→For each failure, follow the **Debugging Workflow** in `.claude/skills/debug-e2e/SKILL.md` (steps 2-5: console.log → test source → entire.log → deep dive). Collect:\\n    52→- What the agent actually did (from console.log)\\n    53→- What was expected (from test source)\\n    54→- CLI-level errors or anomalies (from entire.log)\\n    55→- Repo/checkpoint state (from git-log.txt, git-tree.txt, checkpoint-metadata/)\\n    56→\\n    57→### Step 2: Classify Each Failure\\n    58→\\n    59→Use **re-run results as the primary signal**, supplemented by artifact analysis.\\n    60→\\n    61→#### Re-run signals (strongest):\\n    62→\\n    63→| Original | Re-run 1 | Re-run 2 | Classification |\\n    64→|----------|----------|----------|----------------|\\n    65→| FAIL | FAIL (same error) | FAIL (same error) | **real-bug** OR **flaky (test-bug)** — see below |\\n    66→| FAIL | PASS | PASS | **flaky** |\\n    67→| FAIL | PASS | FAIL | **flaky** (non-deterministic) |\\n    68→| FAIL | FAIL | PASS | **flaky** (non-deterministic) |\\n    69→| FAIL | FAIL (different error) | FAIL (different error) | **needs deeper analysis** — examine artifacts |\\n    70→\\n    71→**Important: Consistent failures can still be `flaky` (test-bug).** When all re-runs fail, check *where* the root cause is:\\n    72→- Root cause in `cmd/entire/cli/` → **real-bug** (product code is broken)\\n    73→- Root cause in `e2e/` (test infra, test helpers, tmux setup, env propagation) → **flaky (test-bug)** — the CLI works fine, the test is broken\\n    74→\\n    75→#### Strong `real-bug` signals (root cause must be in `cmd/entire/cli/`, not `e2e/`):\\n    76→\\n    77→- `entire.log` contains `\\\"level\\\":\\\"ERROR\\\"` or panic/stack traces from CLI code\\n    78→- Checkpoint metadata structurally corrupt (malformed JSON, missing `checkpoint_id`/`strategy`)\\n    79→- Session state file missing or malformed when expected\\n    80→- Hooks did not fire at all (no `hook invoked` log entries)\\n    81→- Shadow/metadata branch has wrong tree structure\\n    82→- Same test fails across 3+ agents with same non-timeout symptom\\n    83→- Error references CLI code (panic in `cmd/entire/cli/`)\\n    84→\\n    85→**Key question:** Is the bug in `cmd/entire/cli/` (product code) or in `e2e/` (test code)? Only the former is a `real-bug`.\\n    86→\\n    87→#### Strong `flaky` signals (unless overridden by real-bug):\\n    88→\\n    89→**Agent behavior (non-deterministic):**\\n    90→- `signal: killed` (timeout)\\n    91→- `context deadline exceeded` or `WaitForCheckpoint.*exceeded deadline`\\n    92→- Agent asked for confirmation instead of acting\\n    93→- Agent created file at wrong path / wrong name\\n    94→- Agent produced no output\\n    95→- Agent committed when it shouldn't have (or vice versa)\\n    96→- Duration near timeout limit\\n    97→\\n    98→**Test-bug (consistent failure, but root cause is in `e2e/` not `cmd/entire/cli/`):**\\n    99→- Agent \\\"Not logged in\\\" / auth errors → test env setup doesn't propagate auth credentials\\n   100→- Env vars not propagated to agent session → tmux/test harness bug\\n   101→- Error references test code (`e2e/`) not CLI code (`cmd/entire/cli/`)\\n   102→- Test helper logic errors (wrong assertions, bad globs, incorrect expected values)\\n   103→- Consistent failure BUT root cause traced to `e2e/` code, not `cmd/entire/cli/`\\n   104→- Test setup/teardown issues (missing git config, temp dir cleanup, port conflicts)\\n   105→\\n   106→#### Ambiguous cases:\\n   107→\\n   108→Read `entire.log` carefully:\\n   109→- If hooks fired correctly and metadata is valid -> lean **flaky**\\n   110→- If hooks fired but produced wrong results -> lean **real-bug**\\n   111→\\n   112→### Step 3: Cross-Agent Correlation\\n   113→\\n   114→Before acting, check correlations using re-run data:\\n   115→- Same test fails for 3+ agents, all re-runs also fail -> strong **real-bug**\\n   116→- Same test fails for multiple agents, but re-runs pass -> **flaky** (shared prompt issue)\\n   117→- One agent fails consistently, others pass -> agent-specific issue (still **real-bug** if re-runs confirm)\\n   118→\\n   119→### Step 4: Take Action\\n   120→\\n   121→Present findings interactively. **Do not** create branches, PRs, or GitHub issues.\\n   122→\\n   123→#### Present Findings Report\\n   124→\\n   125→For each test+agent pair, print a findings block:\\n   126→\\n   127→```\\n   128→## <TestName> (<agent>) — <classification>\\n   129→\\n   130→**Re-run results:** original=FAIL, rerun1=PASS, rerun2=PASS\\n   131→**Evidence:**\\n   132→- <1-2 sentence summary of what went wrong>\\n   133→- <key artifact evidence: entire.log excerpt, console.log excerpt, etc.>\\n   134→```\\n   135→\\n   136→#### For `flaky` failures: describe the proposed fix\\n   137→\\n   138→For agent-behavior flaky issues, fixes typically modify test prompts. For test-bug flaky issues, fixes target `e2e/` infrastructure code (harness setup, helpers, env propagation).\\n   139→\\n   140→```\\n   141→**Proposed fix:** <description>\\n   142→  - File: <path to test file or e2e infrastructure file>\\n   143→  - Change: <what will be modified — e.g., append \\\"Do not ask for confirmation\\\" to prompt, or fix env propagation in NewTmuxSession>\\n   144→```\\n   145→\\n   146→Common flaky fixes:\\n   147→- Agent asked for confirmation -> append \\\"Do not ask for confirmation\\\" to prompt\\n   148→- Agent wrote to wrong path -> be more explicit about paths in prompt\\n   149→- Agent committed when shouldn't -> add \\\"Do not commit\\\" to prompt\\n   150→- Checkpoint wait timeout -> increase timeout argument\\n   151→- Agent timeout (signal: killed) -> increase per-test timeout, simplify prompt\\n   152→- Auth/env not propagated -> fix test harness env setup in `e2e/` code\\n   153→- Test helper bug (wrong assertion, bad glob) -> fix test helper in `e2e/`\\n   154→- tmux session setup issue -> fix `NewTmuxSession` or session config in `e2e/`\\n   155→\\n   156→#### For `real-bug` failures: describe root cause analysis\\n   157→\\n   158→```\\n   159→**Root cause analysis:**\\n   160→  - Component: <hooks | session | checkpoint | strategy | agent>\\n   161→  - Suspected location: <file:function>\\n   162→  - Description: <what's wrong and why>\\n   163→  - Proposed fix: <what code change would address it>\\n   164→```\\n   165→\\n   166→#### Ask the user\\n   167→\\n   168→Prompt the user:\\n   169→\\n   170→> **Should I fix these?**\\n   171→> - [list of tests with classifications]\\n   172→> - You can select all, specific tests, or skip.\\n   173→\\n   174→Wait for user response before proceeding.\\n   175→\\n   176→#### Apply fixes (if user approves)\\n   177→\\n   178→For **flaky** fixes the user approved:\\n   179→1. Apply fixes directly in the working tree (no branch creation)\\n   180→2. Run verification:\\n   181→   ```bash\\n   182→   mise run test:e2e:canary   # Must pass\\n   183→   mise run fmt && mise run lint\\n   184→   ```\\n   185→3. If canary fails, investigate and adjust. Report what happened to the user.\\n   186→\\n   187→For **real-bug** fixes the user approved:\\n   188→1. Apply the fix directly in the working tree (no branch creation)\\n   189→2. Run relevant tests to verify:\\n   190→   ```bash\\n   191→   mise run test        # Unit tests\\n   192→   mise run test:e2e:canary  # Canary tests\\n   193→   ```\\n   194→3. Report results to the user.\\n   195→\\n   196→### Step 5: Summary\\n   197→\\n   198→Print a summary table:\\n   199→```\\n   200→| Test | Agent(s) | Re-runs | Classification | Action Taken |\\n   201→|------|----------|---------|---------------|-------------|\\n   202→| TestFoo | claude-code | FAIL/PASS/PASS | flaky | Fixed in working tree |\\n   203→| TestBar | all agents | FAIL/FAIL/FAIL | real-bug | Fix applied, tests passing |\\n   204→| TestBaz | opencode | FAIL/PASS/FAIL | flaky | Skipped (user declined) |\\n   205→```\\n   206→\"}]},\"uuid\":\"1fb4c6bb-196c-4fae-8108-f92833b3c4df\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-07T00:25:10.739Z\",\"toolUseResult\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"file\":{\"filePath\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli/.claude/skills/e2e-triage/SKILL.md\",\"content\":\"---\\nname: e2e-triage\\ndescription: Triage E2E test failures — run locally with mise, classify flaky vs real bug. Presents findings and applies fixes in-place.\\n---\\n\\n# E2E Triage\\n\\nTriage E2E test failures with **re-run verification**. Analyzes artifacts and re-runs failing tests locally to distinguish flaky from real bugs. Presents findings interactively and applies fixes directly in the working tree.\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Step L1: Parse User Input\\n\\nThe user provides one or more of:\\n- **Test name(s)** — e.g., `TestInteractiveMultiStep`\\n- **`--agent <agent>`** — optional, defaults to all agents that previously failed\\n- **A local artifact path** — skip straight to analysis of existing artifacts\\n\\n**Cost warning:** Real E2E tests consume API tokens. Before running, confirm with the user unless they provided specific test names (implying intent to run).\\n\\n## Step L2: First Run\\n\\n```bash\\nmise run test:e2e --agent <agent> <TestName>\\n```\\n\\nCapture the artifact directory from the `artifacts: <path>` output line.\\n\\n## Step L3: Re-run on Failure\\n\\nIf the test **passes** on first run: report as passing, done for this test.\\n\\nIf the test **fails**: run a **second time** with the same parameters.\\n\\n## Step L4: Tiebreaker (if needed)\\n\\nIf results are **split** (1 pass, 1 fail): run a **third time** as tiebreaker.\\n\\n## Step L5: Collect Results\\n\\nFor each test+agent pair, record: `(test, agent, run_1_result, run_2_result, [run_3_result])`\\n\\nProceed to **Shared Analysis** (Step 1 below).\\n\\n---\\n\\n## Shared Analysis & Classification\\n\\n### Step 1: Analyze Each Failure\\n\\nFor each failure, follow the **Debugging Workflow** in `.claude/skills/debug-e2e/SKILL.md` (steps 2-5: console.log → test source → entire.log → deep dive). Collect:\\n- What the agent actually did (from console.log)\\n- What was expected (from test source)\\n- CLI-level errors or anomalies (from entire.log)\\n- Repo/checkpoint state (from git-log.txt, git-tree.txt, checkpoint-metadata/)\\n\\n### Step 2: Classify Each Failure\\n\\nUse **re-run results as the primary signal**, supplemented by artifact analysis.\\n\\n#### Re-run signals (strongest):\\n\\n| Original | Re-run 1 | Re-run 2 | Classification |\\n|----------|----------|----------|----------------|\\n| FAIL | FAIL (same error) | FAIL (same error) | **real-bug** OR **flaky (test-bug)** — see below |\\n| FAIL | PASS | PASS | **flaky** |\\n| FAIL | PASS | FAIL | **flaky** (non-deterministic) |\\n| FAIL | FAIL | PASS | **flaky** (non-deterministic) |\\n| FAIL | FAIL (different error) | FAIL (different error) | **needs deeper analysis** — examine artifacts |\\n\\n**Important: Consistent failures can still be `flaky` (test-bug).** When all re-runs fail, check *where* the root cause is:\\n- Root cause in `cmd/entire/cli/` → **real-bug** (product code is broken)\\n- Root cause in `e2e/` (test infra, test helpers, tmux setup, env propagation) → **flaky (test-bug)** — the CLI works fine, the test is broken\\n\\n#### Strong `real-bug` signals (root cause must be in `cmd/entire/cli/`, not `e2e/`):\\n\\n- `entire.log` contains `\\\"level\\\":\\\"ERROR\\\"` or panic/stack traces from CLI code\\n- Checkpoint metadata structurally corrupt (malformed JSON, missing `checkpoint_id`/`strategy`)\\n- Session state file missing or malformed when expected\\n- Hooks did not fire at all (no `hook invoked` log entries)\\n- Shadow/metadata branch has wrong tree structure\\n- Same test fails across 3+ agents with same non-timeout symptom\\n- Error references CLI code (panic in `cmd/entire/cli/`)\\n\\n**Key question:** Is the bug in `cmd/entire/cli/` (product code) or in `e2e/` (test code)? Only the former is a `real-bug`.\\n\\n#### Strong `flaky` signals (unless overridden by real-bug):\\n\\n**Agent behavior (non-deterministic):**\\n- `signal: killed` (timeout)\\n- `context deadline exceeded` or `WaitForCheckpoint.*exceeded deadline`\\n- Agent asked for confirmation instead of acting\\n- Agent created file at wrong path / wrong name\\n- Agent produced no output\\n- Agent committed when it shouldn't have (or vice versa)\\n- Duration near timeout limit\\n\\n**Test-bug (consistent failure, but root cause is in `e2e/` not `cmd/entire/cli/`):**\\n- Agent \\\"Not logged in\\\" / auth errors → test env setup doesn't propagate auth credentials\\n- Env vars not propagated to agent session → tmux/test harness bug\\n- Error references test code (`e2e/`) not CLI code (`cmd/entire/cli/`)\\n- Test helper logic errors (wrong assertions, bad globs, incorrect expected values)\\n- Consistent failure BUT root cause traced to `e2e/` code, not `cmd/entire/cli/`\\n- Test setup/teardown issues (missing git config, temp dir cleanup, port conflicts)\\n\\n#### Ambiguous cases:\\n\\nRead `entire.log` carefully:\\n- If hooks fired correctly and metadata is valid -> lean **flaky**\\n- If hooks fired but produced wrong results -> lean **real-bug**\\n\\n### Step 3: Cross-Agent Correlation\\n\\nBefore acting, check correlations using re-run data:\\n- Same test fails for 3+ agents, all re-runs also fail -> strong **real-bug**\\n- Same test fails for multiple agents, but re-runs pass -> **flaky** (shared prompt issue)\\n- One agent fails consistently, others pass -> agent-specific issue (still **real-bug** if re-runs confirm)\\n\\n### Step 4: Take Action\\n\\nPresent findings interactively. **Do not** create branches, PRs, or GitHub issues.\\n\\n#### Present Findings Report\\n\\nFor each test+agent pair, print a findings block:\\n\\n```\\n## <TestName> (<agent>) — <classification>\\n\\n**Re-run results:** original=FAIL, rerun1=PASS, rerun2=PASS\\n**Evidence:**\\n- <1-2 sentence summary of what went wrong>\\n- <key artifact evidence: entire.log excerpt, console.log excerpt, etc.>\\n```\\n\\n#### For `flaky` failures: describe the proposed fix\\n\\nFor agent-behavior flaky issues, fixes typically modify test prompts. For test-bug flaky issues, fixes target `e2e/` infrastructure code (harness setup, helpers, env propagation).\\n\\n```\\n**Proposed fix:** <description>\\n  - File: <path to test file or e2e infrastructure file>\\n  - Change: <what will be modified — e.g., append \\\"Do not ask for confirmation\\\" to prompt, or fix env propagation in NewTmuxSession>\\n```\\n\\nCommon flaky fixes:\\n- Agent asked for confirmation -> append \\\"Do not ask for confirmation\\\" to prompt\\n- Agent wrote to wrong path -> be more explicit about paths in prompt\\n- Agent committed when shouldn't -> add \\\"Do not commit\\\" to prompt\\n- Checkpoint wait timeout -> increase timeout argument\\n- Agent timeout (signal: killed) -> increase per-test timeout, simplify prompt\\n- Auth/env not propagated -> fix test harness env setup in `e2e/` code\\n- Test helper bug (wrong assertion, bad glob) -> fix test helper in `e2e/`\\n- tmux session setup issue -> fix `NewTmuxSession` or session config in `e2e/`\\n\\n#### For `real-bug` failures: describe root cause analysis\\n\\n```\\n**Root cause analysis:**\\n  - Component: <hooks | session | checkpoint | strategy | agent>\\n  - Suspected location: <file:function>\\n  - Description: <what's wrong and why>\\n  - Proposed fix: <what code change would address it>\\n```\\n\\n#### Ask the user\\n\\nPrompt the user:\\n\\n> **Should I fix these?**\\n> - [list of tests with classifications]\\n> - You can select all, specific tests, or skip.\\n\\nWait for user response before proceeding.\\n\\n#### Apply fixes (if user approves)\\n\\nFor **flaky** fixes the user approved:\\n1. Apply fixes directly in the working tree (no branch creation)\\n2. Run verification:\\n   ```bash\\n   mise run test:e2e:canary   # Must pass\\n   mise run fmt && mise run lint\\n   ```\\n3. If canary fails, investigate and adjust. Report what happened to the user.\\n\\nFor **real-bug** fixes the user approved:\\n1. Apply the fix directly in the working tree (no branch creation)\\n2. Run relevant tests to verify:\\n   ```bash\\n   mise run test        # Unit tests\\n   mise run test:e2e:canary  # Canary tests\\n   ```\\n3. Report results to the user.\\n\\n### Step 5: Summary\\n\\nPrint a summary table:\\n```\\n| Test | Agent(s) | Re-runs | Classification | Action Taken |\\n|------|----------|---------|---------------|-------------|\\n| TestFoo | claude-code | FAIL/PASS/PASS | flaky | Fixed in working tree |\\n| TestBar | all agents | FAIL/FAIL/FAIL | real-bug | Fix applied, tests passing |\\n| TestBaz | opencode | FAIL/PASS/FAIL | flaky | Skipped (user declined) |\\n```\\n\",\"numLines\":206,\"startLine\":1,\"totalLines\":206}},\"sourceToolAssistantUUID\":\"9b6a5031-063b-4bad-8649-126f30d72dd8\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"1fb4c6bb-196c-4fae-8108-f92833b3c4df\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"a81178c2-3cee-4c17-bcb1-f86a790fe8fd\",\"version\":\"2.1.71\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/e2e-triage-local-only\",\"slug\":\"luminous-plotting-creek\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01FFt8ZgBbZP7MFz6tUHrpKw\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Now I have a clear picture of the file. Let me apply the changes to Step L1 and add guidance for CI artifact downloads.\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":1,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":3082,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":27741,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":3082},\"output_tokens\":1,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"}},\"requestId\":\"req_011CYnmZ2xb6DPAxsmgPML7t\",\"type\":\"assistant\",\"uuid\":\"ae924657-a72b-4a2d-9341-db7512ca4261\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-07T00:25:14.217Z\"}\n{\"parentUuid\":\"ae924657-a72b-4a2d-9341-db7512ca4261\",\"isSidechain\":false,\"userType\":\"external\",\"cwd\":\"/Users/alisha/Projects/devenv/cli\",\"sessionId\":\"a81178c2-3cee-4c17-bcb1-f86a790fe8fd\",\"version\":\"2.1.71\",\"gitBranch\":\"alisha/e2e-triage-local-only\",\"slug\":\"luminous-plotting-creek\